value.title: 'Defund police' movement drives officers toward Trump

value.excerpt: Halfway through October, President Donald Trump's surprises are sputtering.

value.excerpt: A spokesman for Joe Biden’s campaign said on Thursday he was “glad” Twitter and Facebook censored a New York Post article about Hunter Biden’s business dealings in Ukraine and China, going so far as to suggest that the gag somehow proved the allegations were false.

value.title: Trump administration sets Gulf of Mexico drilling auction for Nov. 18
value.excerpt: The Trump administration on Thursday said it would offer all available areas in the Gulf of Mexico for auction to oil and gas drillers on Nov. 18, the first major test of the offshore sector's appetite for investment since early this year.

value.title: How to Watch, Live Stream Donald Trump's NBC Town Hall in Place of Debate
value.excerpt: The event will be moderated by Today co-host Savannah Guthrie, who will direct a conversation between Trump and Florida voters.

value.title: Pompeo calls tech firms ‘inconsistent’ after censorship of Hunter Biden story
value.excerpt: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Thursday hit tech giants like Twitter and Facebook for what he said was “inconsistent” cracking down on accounts -- a day after the two social media platforms shut down accounts for sharing a New York Post story on Hunter Biden.

value.title: Biden campaign ramping up outreach to Arizona Latinos
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's campaign urged Latino supporters to cast their ballots early on Wednesday.

value.title: Kamala Harris Cancels Campaign Travel After Aide, Flight-Crew Member Test Positive for Coronavirus
value.excerpt: Democratic vice-presidential nominee Kamala Harris is canceling her campaign travel through Sunday after her communications director and a non-staff flight crew member tested positive for coronavirus.

value.title: Will Trump win again? Watch Florida's Sumter County for first election night clue.
value.excerpt: Will Trump win again? Watch Florida's Sumter County for first election night clue. Last week, Democrats took delight in the spectacle of a 500-golf cart flotilla of Joe Biden supporters parading through Florida's largest retirement community en route to turn in their vote-by-mail ballots.

value.title: Trump tweet gave Taliban upper hand in negotiations: Afghan peace official tells Financial Times
value.excerpt: A tweet by President Donald Trump calling for U.S. troops to be home by Christmas has given the insurgent Taliban the upper hand in negotiations, the top Afghanistan peace official told the Financial Times newspaper.

value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's (D) campaign announced late Wednesday that it had raised a massive $383 million during the third quarter of 2020, marking the best period for the campaign so far.

value.title: Biden once again shatters fundraising record with eyepopping $383 million haul last month
value.excerpt: Joe Biden shattered the monthly record for fundraising during a presidential campaign when he hauled in a massive $364.5 million in August.

value.title: Obama: Trump's lack of 'patience' and 'focus' hold back his foreign policy
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama said Wednesday that President Donald Trump lacks the needed "patience" and "focus" to make substantial changes to American foreign policy, previewing a possible attack line as the former President prepares to return to the campaign trail for Democratic nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Biden announces record $383 million fundraising haul for September
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden announced Wednesday evening that his campaign raised a record-breaking $383 million in September, its second straight historic monthly fundraising haul as the campaign nears Election Day.

value.title: Trump directs California GOP to 'fight hard' in court over ballot boxes despite prosecution threat
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday directed Republicans to “fight hard” in court after California’s top election and law enforcement officials, both Democrats, ordered the state GOP to remove unofficial ballot boxes from various locations in three counties by later this week or face prosecution.

value.title: Trump tries to shore up support from big business, Iowans
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump is trying to shore up support from constituencies that not so long ago he thought he had in the bag: big business and voters in the red state of Iowa

value.title: 2020 Daily Trail Markers: Trump and Pence return to critical battleground Michigan this week
value.excerpt: CBS News Battleground Tracker poll shows Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden leading Mr. Trump in the state, 52% to 46% among likely voters.

value.title: Sen. John Kennedy: New Hunter Biden report as serious as 'four heart attacks and a stroke'
value.excerpt: A New York Post report involving newly unearthed emails between Hunter Biden and an executive at Ukrainian energy company Burisma is as serious "as four heart attacks and a stroke,"  Senate Judiciary Committee member John Kennedy, R-La., told "Special Report" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump administration secures release of two American hostages from Yemen
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has secured the release of two American hostages held captive by Houthis in Yemen, Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Wednesday.
